# Repository Licensing

This repository uses multiple licenses by content type.

## 1) Source code and automation

Unless otherwise noted, source code and automation files are licensed under the MIT License.

Scope includes:

- JavaScript, JSON, and configuration files used to build and run the site
- GitHub workflow files
- Build and helper scripts

See LICENSE-CODE for the full MIT license text.

## 2) Written content

Unless otherwise noted, original written content is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0).

Scope includes:

- Blog posts in blog/
- Documentation pages in docs/
- Markdown or MDX pages in src/pages/

See LICENSE-CONTENT for details.

## 3) Third-party assets and exceptions

Third-party assets are not covered by LICENSE-CODE or LICENSE-CONTENT unless explicitly stated.
